Candidate should possess basic knowledge of:
•         Operating systems (Windows)
•         Local Area Networking.
•         Server and workstation hardware.
•         IT security standards and implementation.
•         Knowledge Opera PMS, Micros Point of Sales etc.
According to Carlson Rezidor Hotel Group general IT organization, the candidate is responsible for :
•         Systems administration and operation
•         User administration
•         User support (first level support)
•         User Training
•         License and Vendor Management
The scope of Information technology includes all electronic systems for processing, storage or communication of digital information deployed in the hotel. Including, but not limited to:
•         Front-office systems (PMS),
•         Telephone systems,
•         Point-of-sales systems,
•         Electronic lock systems,
•         Back-office systems,
•         Office Automation and e-mail systems,
•         Guest High Speed Internet services
•         Servers and Personal Computers,
•         Local and Wide Area Networks,
•         Video-systems,
•         Digital Signage systems
•         Smart Phones, other mobile devices,
•         Printers and Fax machines, etc.,
Responsibility and opportunity could grow with the development of the business, for example the prospect of recruiting and managing support staff and some people-management skills, Able to communicate verbally and in writing. Able to hold a presentation and training to a smaller audience, such as the management group, employee groups etc.
Person Specifications
Should be a team leader but also a team member
Have natural Yes I Can! attitude
Good communication skills
Fluent in English, both spoken and written
Flexible and proactive
Creative as well as adventurous and fun-minded person
Have Hands-on management style
Highly responsible and reliable
Ability to work well under pressure in a fast paced environment
Friendly attitude
Interested abd qualified candidate, kindly forward the detailed copy of your resume stating your current/expected salary and availability.
We thank you in advance for your application and we'll get in touch with you within 10 to 12 working days should you be shortlisted.
